      "content": "The term \"fake news\" has become a highly subjective and politicized label, often used to silence opposing viewpoints and discredit sources that don't align with one's own ideology. In reality, most \"fake news\" claims are based on cherry-picked facts, taken out of context, or deliberately misleading, rather than objective falsehoods. The term has become a tool for censorship and propaganda, rather than a genuine attempt to identify and correct false information.",
